<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="106" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 9.</seg></opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">The Secretary to the Admiralty to Mr.
                                    Hammond</persName>.—(Received January 23.)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Admiralty,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-22"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 22, 1864</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> With reference to your letter of
                                yesterday, I am commanded by my lords commissioners of the admiralty
                                to state, for the information of Earl Russell, that Rear-Admiral Sir
                                Baldwin Walker will be called upon to report on the points therein
                                mentioned with regard to the case of the British vessel Saxon,
                                captured at Angra Pequena by the United States steamer
                                Vanderbilt.</p>
                            <p>My lords would suggest that information on this subject might also be
                                obtained from the governor of the Cape of Good Hope.</p>
                            <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>C. PAGET.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>